
Directed & Undirected graphs

    This types of graphs are good to describe traffic flows

    Directed: you can only go on in one direction: one way street, you can only go one way.
    Undirected: Both directions: like a highway between two cities where you can go back and forward

    Facebook has a undirected graph
    When i'm connected to a friend that friend is also connected to me.

    Instagram is more directed
    If i have my profile people can follow me and i can follow people
    if someone follows me i don't automatically follow them.

Weighted graphs & Unweighted graphs:

    with graphs (weighted) you can also have informations in the edges (in the connections between the vertex/node)

    maybe you are going into a trip and want to search the most efficient way to visit sites

    Google Maps use a weighted graph to decide what's the shortest path for you to get there.

    these sort of graphs are used a lot to calculate optimal paths.


Cyclic and Acyclic graphs:

    when you have vertices connected in a circular fashion, it's called cyclic,
    when you can back to the original vertice.

    Acyclic you cant do that.

    Cyclic graphs are really common in weighted graphs (with values in the edges)
    like google maps, most of the time there is a way to get back.
